1. What are position attributes in CSS?

The position property defines how an element is placed on the page.

Types:
static (default)
relative
absolute
fixed
sticky
2. What is Flexbox?

Flexbox (Flexible Box Layout) is a layout system used to align and distribute space among items in a container.

Works in one direction (row or column)
Makes alignment easy (center, space-between, etc.)

👉 Example:

.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
3. Difference between display: none and visibility: hidden
Feature	display: none	visibility: hidden
Visible?	❌ No	❌ No
Space occupied?	❌ No	✅ Yes
Layout affected?	Yes (removed)	No

👉 Simple:

display: none → removes element completely
visibility: hidden → hides but keeps space
4. What is CSS Box Model?

It defines the structure of an element:

6
Parts:
Content
Padding (space inside border)
Border
Margin (space outside border)
5. Difference between padding and margin
Padding	Margin
Inside the element	Outside the element
Affects background	Does NOT affect background
Space between content & border	Space between elements

👉 Example:

div {
  padding: 10px;  /* inside */
  margin: 10px;   /* outside */
}
6. What are pseudo classes (you wrote "sudo classes")?

Pseudo-classes define a special state of an element.

👉 Examples:

:hover → when mouse is over
:active → when clicked
:focus → when input is selected
:first-child
button:hover {
  background-color: red;
}
7. What are semantic and non-semantic elements?
Semantic elements (meaningful)
Clearly describe content
👉 Examples:
<header>, <footer>, <article>, <section>
Non-semantic elements
No meaning
👉 Examples:
<div>, <span>
8. How do we hide an element?

Main ways:

display: none;
visibility: hidden;
opacity: 0;

👉 Most common answer (interview):
display: none

9. Types of position (explained simply)
5
static → default, no special positioning
relative → moves relative to itself
absolute → moves relative to parent
fixed → fixed on screen (does not scroll)
sticky → sticks when scrolling
